en_969721_0	Repeating the practice of appreciating valuable service of retiring Senior Officers, Lieutenant General Shavendra Silva, acting Chief of Defence Staff and Commander of the Army Tuesday (14) invited Major General Wasantha Kumarapperuma, General Officer Commanding, 65 Division to his office on the eve of his retirement and commended him for his contribution to the growth of the Army.
en_969721_1	Lieutenant General Shavendra Silva during the brief interaction recalled past memories and shared a few thoughts with the retiring Major General Kumarapperuma who has served the organization for more than three decades.
en_969721_2	The outgoing Senior Officer also thanked the Commander of the Army for his wishes and the thoughtfulness.
en_969721_3	Towards the end, Lieutenant General Silva awarded a special memento to the retiree as a symbol of appreciation and commendation.
en_969721_4	Major General Wasantha Kamarapperuma of the Sri Lanka Sinha Regiment (SLSR) during his tenure has served many command and staff appointments in his Regiment and the Army.
